{"id":16015,"title":"[Recognizing up as a subject of risk: the conscience of possible harms of tuberculosis].","abstract":"This paper analyzes from the users' perception adherent to treatment, the meanings attributed to the risks of the disease. The qualitative study was developed from the Grounded Theory. Data collection occurred through semi-structured interviews, with 19 users as subjects adhering to tuberculosis treatment. The project was approved by the research ethics committee of UFRGS. Survey participants indicate relational risks such as the possibility of harms that tuberculosis is the interaction of the patient with society, with interference with public and private dimensions of everyday life. The recognition of the participants as subjects of risks was part of a process that is producing identities, making them sought an image of the subject concerned with his care and the care of the other, preserving their personal relationships and interaction in society.","date":"2014-08-01","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25080710","annotations":[{"name":"Perception","weight":0.832197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perception"},{"name":"Ethics","weight":0.767518,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethics"},{"name":"Interpersonal relationship","weight":0.69478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpersonal_relationship"},{"name":"Research","weight":0.669249,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research"},{"name":"Society","weight":0.603184,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Society"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.597719,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Grounded theory","weight":0.415136,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grounded_theory"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.324431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.268093,"wikiped